- `ChatOptions` - (`Microsoft.Extensions.AI.ChatOptions`) - Base chat configuration
- `ChatHistoryProvider` - Custom history provider
- `AIContextProviders` - Array of context providers
- `UseProvidedChatClientAsIs` - Skip automatic wrapping (bool)
- `ClearOnChatHistoryProviderConflict` - Auto-clear conflicting history (bool)
- `WarnOnChatHistoryProviderConflict` - Log warnings on conflicts (bool)
- `ThrowOnChatHistoryProviderConflict` - Throw exceptions on conflicts (bool)
- `RequirePerServiceCallChatHistoryPersistence` - Enforce per-call persistence (bool)

---

### 3. **AGENT BASE CLASS & INVOCATION** - `AIAgent`

**Base Class Methods (all agents inherit from this):**

```csharp
// Core overloads for RunAsync - all return Task<AgentResponse>
RunAsync(AgentSession, AgentRunOptions, CancellationToken)
RunAsync(string message, AgentSession, AgentRunOptions, CancellationToken)
RunAsync(ChatMessage, AgentSession, AgentRunOptions, CancellationToken)
RunAsync(IEnumerable<ChatMessage> messages, AgentSession, AgentRunOptions, CancellationToken)

// Streaming variants - all return IAsyncEnumerable<AgentResponseUpdate>
RunStreamingAsync(AgentSession, AgentRunOptions, CancellationToken)
RunStreamingAsync(string, AgentSession, AgentRunOptions, CancellationToken)
RunStreamingAsync(ChatMessage, AgentSession, AgentRunOptions, CancellationToken)
RunStreamingAsync(IEnumerable<ChatMessage>, AgentSession, AgentRunOptions, CancellationToken)

// Structured output variants - all return Task<AgentResponse<T>>
RunAsync<T>(AgentSession, JsonSerializerOptions, AgentRunOptions, CancellationToken)
RunAsync<T>(string, AgentSession, JsonSerializerOptions, AgentRunOptions, CancellationToken)
// ... and more variants with ChatMessage/IEnumerable<ChatMessage>

// Session management
CreateSessionAsync(CancellationToken) → Task<AgentSession>
DeserializeSessionAsync(JsonElement, JsonSerializerOptions, CancellationToken) → Task<AgentSession>
GetService(Type serviceType, object serviceKey) → object
```

---

### 4. **RUN OPTIONS** - `ChatClientAgentRunOptions` / `AgentRunOptions`

```csharp
public class ChatClientAgentRunOptions : AgentRunOptions
{
    // Constructor
    public ChatClientAgentRunOptions(ChatOptions chatOptions)

    // Properties
    public ChatOptions ChatOptions { get; set; }
    public Func<IChatClient, Task<IChatClient>> ChatClientFactory { get; set; }

    // Methods
    public ChatClientAgentRunOptions Clone()
}
```

---

### 5. **RESPONSE TYPES**

#### **`AgentResponse`**
```csharp
// Constructors
public AgentResponse()
public AgentResponse(ChatMessage message)
public AgentResponse(ChatResponse chatResponse)

// Properties
public IList<ChatMessage> Messages { get; }
public string Text { get; }  // Extracts text from first message

// Access patterns
response.Messages.FirstOrDefault()
response.ToString()  // Same as Text
```

#### **`AgentResponseUpdate`** (for streaming)
- Similar structure for incremental updates

#### **`AgentResponse<T>`** (structured output)
- Generic version with parsed result

---

### 6. **SESSION MANAGEMENT** - `AgentSession`

**Key Purpose:**
- Maintains conversation state across multiple runs
- Stores chat history, memories, and custom state
- Can be serialized/deserialized for persistence

**Methods:**
- Session is created via `agent.CreateSessionAsync(cancellationToken)`
- Session is updated automatically during `RunAsync()` calls
- Support for serialization to JSON for storage

---

### 7. **CHAT MESSAGE & ROLE** - `Microsoft.Extensions.AI`

#### **`ChatMessage`**
```csharp
// Constructors
public ChatMessage()  // Defaults to User role
public ChatMessage(ChatRole role, string content)
public ChatMessage(ChatRole role, IList<AIContent> contents)

// Properties
public ChatRole Role { get; set; }
public IList<AIContent> Contents { get; set; }
public string AuthorName { get; set; }
public DateTimeOffset? CreatedAt { get; set; }

// Methods
public ChatMessage Clone()  // Shallow clone
```

#### **`ChatRole`** (struct with static properties)
```csharp
public static ChatRole System { get; }      // System instructions
public static ChatRole Assistant { get; }   // AI responses
public static ChatRole User { get; }        // User input
public static ChatRole Tool { get; }        // Tool/function results
